===Climate===
Aberdeen features an [[oceanic climate]] ([[Köppen climate classification|Köppen]] ''Cfb''). Aberdeen is far milder than one might expect for its northern location. During the winter, especially throughout December, the length of the day is very short, averaging 6 hours and 40 minutes between sunrise and sunset at the Winter Solstice. As winter progresses, the length of the day grows fairly quickly, to 8 hours and 20 minutes by the end of January. As summer begins, the days will be around 18 hours long, having 17 hours and 57 minutes between sunrise and sunset, with Nautical Twilight lasting the entire night. Temperatures at this time of year will be hovering around 17&amp;nbsp;°C during the day.
