{{ThisDateInRecentYears}} 
{{Day}}

==Events==
*[[49 BC]] &amp;ndash; [[Julius Caesar]]'s [[general]] [[Gaius Scribonius Curio]] is defeated in the [[Battle of the Bagradas River (49 BC)|Second Battle of the Bagradas River]] by the [[Numidians]] under [[Publius Attius Varus]] and King [[Juba I of Numidia|Juba]] of [[Numidia]]. Curio commits suicide to avoid capture.
*  [[79]] &amp;ndash; [[Mount Vesuvius]] erupts. The cities of [[Pompeii]], [[Herculaneum]], and [[Stabiae]] are buried in volcanic ash (note: this traditional date has been challenged, and many scholars believe that the event occurred on October 24).
* [[410]] &amp;ndash; The [[Visigoths]] under [[Alaric I|Alaric]] begin to [[Sack of Rome (410)|pillage Rome]].
*[[1200]] &amp;ndash; King [[John of England]], signee of the first [[Magna Carta]], marries [[Isabella of Angouleme]] in [[Bordeaux Cathedral]].
*[[1215]] &amp;ndash; [[Pope Innocent III]] declares [[Magna Carta]] invalid.
*[[1349]] &amp;ndash; Six thousand [[Jews]] are killed in [[Mainz]] after being blamed for the [[bubonic plague]].
*[[1391]] &amp;ndash; [[Jews]] are massacred in [[Palma de Mallorca]].
*[[1456]] &amp;ndash; The printing of the [[Gutenberg Bible]] is completed.
*[[1511]] &amp;ndash; [[Afonso de Albuquerque]] of [[Portugal]] conquers [[Malacca]], the capital of the [[Sultanate of Malacca]].
*[[1561]] &amp;ndash; [[William the Silent|Willem of Orange]] marries duchess [[Anna of Saxony]].
*[[1572]] &amp;ndash; [[St. Bartholomew's Day Massacre]]: On the orders of king [[Charles IX of France]], a massacre of [[Huguenot]]s (French [[Protestant]]s) begins.
*[[1608]] &amp;ndash; The first official [[England|English]] representative to [[India]] lands in [[Surat]].
*[[1662]] &amp;ndash; The [[Act of Uniformity 1662|Act of Uniformity]] requires England to accept the [[Book of Common Prayer]].
*[[1682]] &amp;ndash; [[William Penn]] receives the area that is now the state of [[Delaware]], and adds it to his [[colony]] of [[Pennsylvania]].
*[[1690]] &amp;ndash; [[Kolkata|Calcutta]], [[India]] is founded.
*[[1812]] &amp;ndash; [[Peninsula War]]: A coalition of [[Spain|Spanish]], [[United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland|British]], and [[Kingdom of Portugal|Portuguese]] forces succeed in lifting the two-and-a-half-year-long [[Siege of Cádiz]].
*[[1814]] &amp;ndash; [[United Kingdom|British]] troops invade [[Washington, D.C.]] and burn down the [[White House]] and several other buildings.
*[[1815]] &amp;ndash; The modern [[Constitution of the Netherlands]] is signed.
*[[1816]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of St. Louis#1816 - Ottawa, Ojibwa, and Potawatomi|Treaty of St. Louis]] is signed in [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]], [[Missouri]].
*[[1820]] &amp;ndash; [[Constitutionalism|Constitutionalist]] [[History of Portugal#Crises of the nineteenth century|insurrection]] at [[Porto|Oporto]], [[Portugal]].
*[[1821]] &amp;ndash; The [[Treaty of Córdoba]] is signed in [[Córdoba, Veracruz|Córdoba]], now in [[Veracruz (state)|Veracruz]], [[Mexico]], concluding the [[Mexican War of Independence]] from [[Spain]].
*[[1831]] &amp;ndash; [[Charles Darwin]] is asked to travel on {{HMS|Beagle}}.
*[[1857]] &amp;ndash; The [[Panic of 1857]] begins, setting off one of the most severe economic crises in United States history.
&lt;!--*[[1858]] &amp;ndash; In [[Richmond, Virginia|Richmond]], [[Virginia]], 90 blacks are arrested for learning. - needs to be explained/expanded--&gt;
*[[1870]] &amp;ndash; The [[Wolseley Expedition]] reaches [[Manitoba]] to end the [[Red River Rebellion]].
*[[1875]] &amp;ndash; [[Captain Matthew Webb]] became first person to swim the [[English Channel]]
*[[1891]] &amp;ndash; [[Thomas Edison]] patents the motion picture camera.
*[[1898]] &amp;ndash; [[Mikhail Nikolayevich Muravyov|Count Muravyov]], [[Foreign Minister of Russia]] presents a ''rescript'' that convoked the [[Hague Conventions (1899 and 1907)|First Hague Peace Conference]].
*[[1902]] &amp;ndash; A statue of [[Joan of Arc]] is unveiled in [[Saint-Pierre-le-Moûtier]].
*[[1909]] &amp;ndash; Workers start pouring concrete for the [[Panama Canal]].
*[[1912]] &amp;ndash; [[Alaska]] becomes a [[United States]] territory.
*[[1914]] &amp;ndash; [[World War I]]: [[Germany|German]] troops capture [[Namur (city)|Namur]].
*[[1929]] &amp;ndash; Second day of two-day [[1929 Hebron massacre|Hebron massacre]] during the [[1929 Palestine riots]]: [[Palestinian people|Arab]] attacks on the [[Jewish]] community in [[Hebron]] in the [[British Mandate of Palestine]], result in the death of 65-68 Jews and the remaining Jews being forced to leave the city.
*[[1931]] &amp;ndash; [[France]] and the [[Soviet Union]] sign a neutrality/no attack treaty.
*  1931   &amp;ndash; Resignation of the [[United Kingdom]]'s [[Second Labour Government]]. Formation of the [[UK National Government]].
*[[1932]] &amp;ndash; [[Amelia Earhart]] becomes the first woman to fly across the [[United States]] non-stop (from [[Los Angeles]] to [[Newark, New Jersey|Newark]], [[New Jersey]]).
*[[1933]] &amp;ndash; The [[Crescent (Amtrak)|Crescent Limited]] train derails in [[Washington, D.C.]], after the [[Amtrak Railroad Anacostia Bridge|bridge]] it is crossing is washed out by the [[1933 Chesapeake–Potomac hurricane]].
*[[1936]] &amp;ndash; The [[Australian Antarctic Territory]] is created.
*[[1937]] &amp;ndash; In the Spanish Civil War, the [[Basque Army]] surrenders to the Italian [[Corpo Truppe Volontarie]] following the [[Santoña Agreement]].
*[[1942]] &amp;ndash; [[World War II]]: The [[Battle of the Eastern Solomons]]. [[Japan]]ese [[aircraft carrier]] ''[[Japanese aircraft carrier Ryūjō|Ryūjō]]'' is sunk and [[United States|US]] carrier {{USS|Enterprise|CV-6|6}} heavily damaged.
*[[1944]] &amp;ndash; World War II: Allied troops begin [[Liberation of Paris|the attack on Paris]].
*[[1949]] &amp;ndash; The treaty creating [[NATO]] goes into effect.
*[[1950]] &amp;ndash; [[Edith Sampson]] becomes the first black [[United States|U.S.]] delegate to the [[United Nations]].
*[[1954]] &amp;ndash; The [[Communist Control Act]] goes into effect. The [[American Communist Party]] is outlawed.
*  1954   &amp;ndash; [[Getúlio Dornelles Vargas]], president of [[Brazil]], commits [[suicide]] and is succeeded by [[João Café Filho]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[Buddhist crisis]]: As a result of the [[Xa Loi Pagoda raids]], the [[US State Department]] [[Cable 243|cables]] the [[US Embassy, Saigon|US Embassy]] in [[Saigon]] to encourage [[Army of the Republic of Vietnam]] generals to [[1963 South Vietnamese coup|launch a coup]] against President [[Ngo Dinh Diem]] if he did not remove his brother [[Ngo Dinh Nhu]].
*[[1963]] &amp;ndash; [[Don Schollander]] swims the 200-metre freestyle in less than 2 minutes for the first time, in a world record time of 1:58.
*[[1967]] &amp;ndash; Led by [[Abbie Hoffman]], a group of [[hippies]] temporarily disrupt trading at the [[NYSE]] by throwing dollar bills from the viewing gallery, causing trading to cease as brokers scramble to grab them.
*[[1968]] &amp;ndash; [[France]] explodes its first [[hydrogen bomb]], thus becoming the world's fifth nuclear power.
*[[1981]] &amp;ndash; [[Mark David Chapman]] is sentenced to 20 years to life in prison for murdering [[John Lennon]].
*[[1989]] &amp;ndash; [[Colombia]]n [[drug baron]]s declare &quot;total war&quot; on the [[Government of Colombia|Colombian government]].
*  1989   &amp;ndash; [[Cincinnati Reds]] [[Manager (baseball)|manager]] [[Pete Rose]] is banned from [[baseball]] for gambling by [[Commissioner of Baseball (MLB)|Commissioner]] [[A. Bartlett Giamatti]].
*[[1991]] &amp;ndash; [[Mikhail Gorbachev]] resigns as head of the [[Communist Party of the Soviet Union]].
*  1991   &amp;ndash; [[Ukraine]] [[Declaration of Independence of Ukraine|declares itself independent]] from the [[Soviet Union]].
*  1992   &amp;ndash; [[Hurricane Andrew]] hits [[South Florida]] as a Category 5 [[Tropical Cyclone|Hurricane]].
*[[1994]] &amp;ndash; Initial accord between [[Israel]] and the [[PLO]] about partial self-rule of the [[palestinian people|Palestinian]]s on the [[West Bank]].
*[[1995]] &amp;ndash; Computer software developer [[Microsoft]] releases its [[Windows 95]] [[operating system]].
*[[1998]] &amp;ndash; First [[RFID]] human implantation tested in the [[United Kingdom]].
*[[2001]] &amp;ndash; [[Air Transat Flight 236]] runs out of fuel over the [[Atlantic Ocean]] (en route to [[Lisbon]] from [[Toronto]]) and makes an emergency landing in the [[Azores]].
*[[2004]] &amp;ndash; Eighty-nine passengers die after [[Russian aircraft bombings of August 2004|two airliners explode]] after flying out of [[Domodedovo International Airport]], near [[Moscow]]. The explosions are caused by suicide bombers (reportedly female) from the [[Russia]]n [[Republic of Chechnya]].
*[[2006]] &amp;ndash; The [[International Astronomical Union]] (IAU) [[2006 definition of planet|redefines the term &quot;planet&quot;]] such that [[Pluto]] is now considered a [[Dwarf Planet]].

